-- Enel CEO Conti Sticks to Target of 45 Billion-Euro Debt in 2010, Sole Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-08T06:23:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/enel-ceo-conti-sticks-to-target-of-45-billion-euro-debt-in-2010-sole-says.html
Enel SpA  is sticking to a plan to
reduce debt to 45 billion euros ($63 billion) by the end of the
year, Il Sole 24 Ore reported, citing a speech by Chief
Executive Officer  Fulvio Conti .  Enel will cut  debt  with cash from asset sales of 3.5
billion euros and a 3 billion-euro initial public offering of
the Enel Green Power division, the Italian newspaper said,
citing the speech Conti gave to bankers in Milan on Oct. 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
